<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Dead to Play at Forum: The death of a fan who clashed with police at the 
Forum in Inglewood during a Grateful Dead concert last December won't change 
the group's plans to play there again in February. The Grateful Dead will 
perform at the Forum Feb. 9, 10 and 11, a band spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
In December a three-night series of shows by the band ended with the death of a 
fan who stopped breathing while handcuffed in the back of a police car. Patrick 
Shanahan, 19, died after arrested on suspicion of being under the influence of 
drugs. An autopsy later determined Shanahan died from compression of the neck 
caused by a carotid neck hold and the death was ruled a homicide. The incident 
is still under investigation by the Los Angeles County District Attorney's 
Office. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
