<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EL CAJON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An El Cajon man convicted of involuntary manslaughter in the death of his 
girlfriend's 18-month-old son was sentenced Monday to nine years in state 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
Benjamin Chloupek, 26, was given the maximum term by San Diego Superior Court 
Judge William Kennedy, who also fined him $100. 
</P>
<P>
A jury on Dec. 12 found Chloupek not guilty of murdering Jeffri Brown, but 
found him guilty of manslaughter, child abuse and inflicting corporal injury on 
a child. 
</P>
<P>
Chloupek testified that the boy must have received his head injuries when he 
fell off a water bed on April 13, 1988, but medical experts told jurors the 
injuries probably occurred in a violent shaking or beating. 
</P>
<P>
The boy was taken to a hospital and died April 20, 1988. Chloupek's former 
girlfriend, Donna McLane, testified against Chloupek at the trial, saying she 
left her son in his care at their El Cajon apartment when she went to a video 
store. 
</P>
<P>
McLane told jurors Chloupek at first told her at the hospital that the boy 
choked on something and later attributed the injuries to the fall. 
</P>
<P>
McLane told Probation Department officials she was not pleased with the verdict 
and wished her former boyfriend could be sent to prison for life, saying he had 
planned the crime. 
</P>
