<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SANTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santee woman and her 2-year-old daughter were killed Sunday night, apparently 
by the woman's estranged husband, who then turned the gun on himself, the San 
Diego County Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
The bodies of Sherry Lucern Battaglia, 41; Kelly Renee Battaglia, 2, and Joseph 
Frances Battaglia, 32, were found at 6:55 p.m. by Sherry Battaglia's family, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Sherry's father, mother and sisters went to the apartment in the 9400 block of 
Lake Canyon Road to take her and Kelly to dinner for Sherry's birthday. When no 
one answered the door, Irving Knight, Sherry Battaglia's father, climbed 
through a window in the back of the house and found the bodies in the bedroom, 
sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The mother and daughter were found in bed. Joseph Battaglia was on the bedroom 
floor with an apparently self-inflicted gunshot to the head. A .38-caliber 
pistol was found nearby, Sheriff's Sgt. Manuel Castillo said. 
</P>
<P>
Joseph and Sherry Battaglia had been separated for several months, Castillo 
said, but authorities are unsure what led to the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
"The whys and why nots, we may never know," Castillo said. 
</P>
