<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: INVESTOR GROUP BOOSTS SHARE IN ATI MEDICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Washington, D.C., investor group raised its stake in ATI Medical Inc. to 8.1% 
of the Glendale company's stock from 5.2%. 
</P>
<P>
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Roxbury Partners and 
its two general partners, Christopher S. Middendorf and Jonathan Bowers, said 
they bought an additional 152,600 shares, giving them a total of 431,000 shares 
of ATI, which rents medical equipment to hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
The latest stock was bought between Nov. 14 and Jan. 12, at prices ranging from 
$7.50 to $10.375 a share, the filing stated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
