<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bowie Tours: David Bowie will kick off a five-continent world tour March 4 in 
Quebec, Canada, with U.S. dates planned for the summer, the singer was 
scheduled to announce at a London press conference today. 
</P>
<P>
The "Sound + Vision" tour will be a retrospective of the singer's career, tied 
into the CD releases of his catalogue scheduled to take place throughout the 
year. A novel aspect of the tour is that fans will be able to help choose the 
tour songs by registering their favorites through a special interactive 
telephone line that will be opened today. The U.S. number is (900) BOWIE90. 
Bowie will be backed on the tour by a quartet led by guitarist Adrian Belew. 
BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Bowie 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
