31 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRANSIT NOMINEE NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush announced Monday that he will nominate James Kolstad as chairman 
of the National Transportation Safety Board. Kolstad has been serving as acting 
chairman since 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
NATIONAL TRANSPORTATION SAFETY BOARD; UNITED STATES -- GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS; 
KOLSTAD, JAMES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012390-0095 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 165894 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
January 23, 1990, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
