<HEADLINE>
<P>
5TH NAVIGATION SATELLITE TO BE PLACED IN ORBIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KENNEDY SPACE CENTER, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Air Force announced Monday that it will launch the fifth of a new type of 
military navigation satellite Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The $65-million Navstar satellite is to be carried aloft by a Delta 2 rocket to 
join a network of spacecraft that can tell American and allied military forces 
where they are to within 50 feet of any location, regardless of weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
