<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW CHIEF FOR N.Y. POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Houston Police Chief Lee Brown was sworn in Monday as New York's 36th 
police commissioner. Brown said: "I will pledge my most earnest and most 
diligent effort in lessening the impact of drugs on all the city's 
neighborhoods." He also acknowledged the city's budget crisis, saying it may 
not be possible to expand the force for some time. 
</P>
