</P>
<P>
RECYCLING DRIVE AIDS COMMUNITY GROUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A recycling drive sponsored by two community groups will be held Saturday in 
the Target Store parking lot at Alicia Parkway and Charlinda Drive. 
</P>
<P>
From 9 a.m. to noon, volunteers from the Laguna Hills Community Assn. and the 
Aegean Hills Homeowners Assn. will accept plastic soda bottles, glass 
containers, newspapers and aluminum. 
</P>
<P>
Businesses are asked to save computer print-out paper. Residents should bundle 
newspapers in paper bags. Phone books, paperback books and magazines cannot be 
recycled. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds will provide scholarships for local high school students and will help 
finance newsletters for the community groups. 
</P>
