<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: REBOUNDING WHIZ HARRY GOES OVERBOARD THIS TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Because she is 6-feet-2 and starts at center for Woodbridge High School, Deanna 
Harry is bound to get rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
But last week, Harry found herself putting the basketball through the hoop and 
not just grabbing the ones that bounced off it. 
</P>
<P>
Harry, The Times' Athlete of the Week, had 29 points, 23 in the first half, and 
16 rebounds to lead Woodbridge in a 69-38 victory over Trabuco Hills Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"I knew I had scored over 15 by halftime, but I didn't think it was that much," 
Harry said. "My role on the team is rebounding. But (Trabuco Hills) was playing 
a defense designed to stop our guards, so I got a lot of baskets." 
</P>
<P>
Harry had 21 rebounds in a 65-31 victory over Laguna Hills Thursday and had 20 
more in a 76-52 nonleague victory over Estancia Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
What's with the big week? 
</P>
<P>
"Away games," Harry said. "I don't know what it is exactly. On the bus ride 
over there I have time to think about the game and visualize. When we play at 
home we talk more before the game." 
</P>
<P>
Now people are starting to talk more after the game too. 
</P>
<P>
"She came out for basketball on a whim as a 5-9 freshman and grew so fast in 
the next year and a half -- you couldn't believe it," Woodbridge Coach Eric 
Bangs said. "She's still a little gangly . . . but she works hard on footwork 
and positioning." 
</P>
<P>
TOP PERFORMERS 
</P>
<P>
La Habra's Leslie Ferguson scored 48 points in two games. 
</P>
<P>
The guard tandem of Michelle Harris and Valerie Ruiz led Kennedy to two 
victories. Harris had 42 points and seven steals in the two games and Ruiz had 
a total of 51 points. 
</P>
<P>
Amy Jalewalia had 33 points and seven rebounds to lead La Quinta to a 64-30 
victory over Los Amigos Wednesday, and had 32 points, nine rebounds and six 
assists in an 82-39 victory over Garden Grove Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman Amber Parkinson had eight goals in three soccer matches for Orange 
Lutheran, including three goals in one game twice. 
</P>
<P>
Laurie Sallinger set an Orange High School record for assists in a game when 
she had 11 assists and eight points against Laguna Beach Tuesday. Sallinger 
also had seven assists and 10 points in a 62-53 victory over Costa Mesa on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
In a 56-43 victory over Esperanza, Wanda Sequeira had 13 points and seven 
assists to set Tustin's single-season assist record at 145, breaking the mark 
set in 1979 by Mary Hegarty. 
</P>
<P>
Deanna Harry 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge High 
</P>
<P>
* Position: Center 
</P>
<P>
* Height, Weight, Class: 6-2, 147, Junior 
</P>
<P>
* Last Week: Harry had 52 points and 57 rebounds in three games. 
</P>
<P>
* Season: Harry is averaging 10.2 points, 13.4 rebounds and 3.5 blocked shots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
