</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUCHAREST, Romania 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The new government today postponed the first democratic elections in more than 
four decades until May 20 because fledgling opposition parties asked for more 
time to organize, a senior official said. 
</P>
<P>
Dimitru Mazilu, a senior member of the governing National Salvation Front, also 
said members of the front will run for Parliament. He said United Nations 
observers will be asked to monitor the balloting, which had been planned for 
April. 
</P>
