<HEADLINE>
<P>
3M REPORTS 7.8% HIKE IN ANNUAL EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MAPLEWOOD, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Minnesota Mining &amp; Manufacturing Co. said today that its earnings increased 
7.4% in the fourth quarter and 7.8% for the year. 
</P>
<P>
For the three months ended Dec. 31, the company -- also known as 3M -- earned 
$292 million, or $1.31 a share, compared to $272 million, or $1.21 a share, in 
the same period a year ago. Fourth-quarter sales rose to $2.95 billion from 
$2.75 billion in 1988. 
</P>
